@jreback I don't think a deprecation is needed? It is fully new API, so I wouldn't add things we will remove shortly. 
It just means that not all `pd.rolling_mean(..)` translates exactly to a `df.rolling(..).mean(..)`, but I don't think that is a problem.

In some way I also like that `resample` would look more like `groupby` and now `rolling`, but this is indeed more controversial (more breaking). But maybe let's leave that discussion for a separate issue? (it is already complicated enough here :-))

@jorisvandenbossche the old API is wrapping the new API. This cleans up a massive amount of code, which was a secondary goal here. 

I _can_ do this to allow the existing `pd.rolling_*` to accept `freq`/`how` but not the new ones I think. 
But not really sure this is that big of a deal. In 0.19.0 we just drop these new deprecations (along with `pd.rolling_*`

@jonblunt 
you mean something like this?

```
def rolling_median(arr, window):
    return Series(arr).rolling(window=window).median().values
```
